{"article_id":"Mps7uuOqoFwMR1fk","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Republican presidential candidate Mitt Romney was in New Hampshire on Friday , back at the farm","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"where he launched his presidential campaign one year ago .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"`` In the days ahead , we 'll be traveling on what are often called the backroads of America , ''","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"he said .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"`` But I think","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"our tour is going to take us along what I 'll call the backbone of America . ''","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"It was the first stop on a five-day bus tour","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"that will take him to small towns .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"The former Massachusetts governor 's campaign is calling it the `` Every Town Counts '' tour .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Even though rural communities appear solidly Republican these days ,","depth":4},{"id":10,"text":"both presidential candidates are trying to win over voters there .","depth":4},{"id":11,"text":"Romney and President Obama are both ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"let 's be honest ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"city slickers .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"That 's a big change for the American presidency ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"says Dee Davis , president of the Center for Rural Strategies .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"`` If it 's [ Ronald ] Reagan on a horse or [ Bill ] Clinton , the man from Hope","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"[ Ark . ] ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"there 's always been this kind of visual narrative or this story","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"to be president","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"you had to be able to handle the wilderness , be comfortable outside of the city .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"It 's just part of the lore , ''","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"he says .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"You 're not likely to see Romney or Obama in a cowboy hat very often .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"But both men are trying to appeal to the folks","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"who live in small towns , traditionally Republican strongholds . `` It 's been an extraordinary priority","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"and the proof of that is the fact","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"that the president established the Rural Council , ''","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"says Agriculture Secretary Tom Vilsack .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"The Rural Council ,","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"which Vilsack runs ,","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"is a group of Cabinet members","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"who meet","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"to talk about policies","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"aimed specifically at rural America .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"This week the council put out a report","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"documenting improvements in the agricultural economy .","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"`` In that report is the plan ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"if you will ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"for revitalizing the rural economy .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"We have n't had a plan in the past .","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"We now do , ''","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"Vilsack explains .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"The administration 's plan talks about increasing exports ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"producing biofuels","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"and giving low-interest loans to small businesses in rural America .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"Exports are already way up over the past few years .","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Farmers are seeing record profits .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"Vilsack says","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"that 's a sign of Obama administration success","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"at helping rural America .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"Jim Talent , a former senator from Missouri","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"who now advises the Romney campaign ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"disagrees .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"`` Exports are up .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"That 's in part because of the weak dollar","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"- and I guess","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"the administration can claim some credit for that .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"I mean ,","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"the dollar 's weak","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"because the economy 's weak , ''","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Talent says .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"Over these five days , Romney will visit six swing states","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"that went for Obama four years ago .","depth":5},{"id":65,"text":"But he 'll focus on the small towns in those states","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"that went Republican last time ,","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"in hopes","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"of tipping the whole state into the red column this time .","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"Talent says","depth":4},{"id":70,"text":"during this bus tour Romney will lay out his ideas","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"to help rural America","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"- more oil and natural gas drilling , lower taxes and deficit reduction .","depth":6},{"id":73,"text":"`` Folks in rural America understand","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"you ca n't borrow your way to prosperity ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"and they know that for themselves ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"and they know it for the federal government as well , ''","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"says Talent .","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"During the primary season , Romney consistently underperformed in small towns .","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"Republican rivals Rick Santorum and Newt Gingrich often beat him in those areas .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"So Romney has some work to do in rural America .","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"According to Davis at the Center for Rural Strategies ,","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"in 2008 , Obama lost rural counties by a smaller margin","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"than past Democratic presidential candidates John Kerry or Al Gore did .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"`` Obama tightened the race , ''","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"says Davis .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"`` He lost rural by about 7 percent in the swing states .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"If he could do that again this time ,","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"he would win in a walk .","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"But at this point , rural looks pretty tough . ''","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"Here 's why Davis says that :","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"In 2008 , rural districts in Congress were split about evenly between Democrats and Republicans .","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"But in 2010 , a Republican wave washed across those districts .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"Nationally , Republicans won 60 House seats in 2010 .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Two-thirds of those wins came from rural America .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"So the small towns","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"that Romney is visiting these next five days","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"are red","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"and getting redder .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"The Republican candidate just needs to keep that momentum going .","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"Obama has the more difficult task","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"of moving the rural trend lines in the opposite direction .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":203,"left":164,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":110,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":110,"left":103,"right":109,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":106,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":104,"right":105,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":108,"left":107,"right":8,"r